VALUES
(44, 11, 14, 44, 16, 15, 15, 'thy house', 'Salvation and Household Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation extending to entire households. In Acts 11:14, the promise of salvation is directed to ''thy house,'' while Acts 16:15 shows a household being baptized, indicating a communal aspect of faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 1, 17, 7, 7, 'all thy house shall be saved', 'Covenant and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation for households in both passages. Acts 11:14 speaks of salvation for ''all thy house,'' while Genesis 17:7 establishes a covenant with ''thy seed after thee,'' indicating a promise that extends to future generations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 43, 20, 31, 31, 'shall be saved', 'Salvation through belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through belief in Jesus. Acts 11:14 emphasizes the words that lead to salvation, while John 20:31 states that belief in Jesus brings life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 62, 5, 9, 13, 'words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and eternal life found in both passages. Acts 11:14 speaks of words that lead to salvation, while 1 John 5:11-12 emphasizes that eternal life is found in the Son, linking belief in Christ to salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 1, 18, 19, 19, 'thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and Household Obedience', 'This connection highlights the importance of household faithfulness in both passages. Acts 11:14 speaks of salvation for a household, while Genesis 18:19 emphasizes Abraham''s role in guiding his household to keep the way of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 19, 19, 7, 11, 'words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through the words of the Lord. Both passages emphasize the importance of divine instruction in leading to spiritual transformation and ultimate salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 19, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Holy Spirit Events', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Holy Ghost upon believers, indicating a significant moment of empowerment. The phrase ''Holy Ghost came on them'' in Acts 19:6 parallels the experience described in Acts 11:15, highlighting a consistent theme of divine presence.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 2, 2, 12, 'Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the falling of the Holy Ghost in both passages. Acts 11:15 refers to the Holy Ghost falling on the Gentiles, paralleling the initial outpouring of the Spirit in Acts 2:2-12.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 10, 34, 46, 'the Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the falling of the Holy Ghost on believers. In Acts 10:46, the Holy Ghost falls on Gentiles, while Acts 11:15 recalls this event as a significant moment for the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 4, 31, 31, 'Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of Holy Spirit Experiences', 'Both passages emphasize the filling of the Holy Ghost and the resulting boldness in speaking. Acts 11:15 refers to the Holy Ghost falling on individuals, similar to the filling described in Acts 4:31, highlighting a shared experience of empowerment by the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 44, 1, 5, 5, 'ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from John''s water baptism to the baptism with the Holy Ghost. This connection highlights the fulfillment of Jesus'' promise regarding the coming of the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 41, 1, 8, 8, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism, specifically the transition from water baptism to baptism with the Holy Ghost. Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus in this spiritual baptism.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 20, 1, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Spirit and Baptism', 'This connection highlights the theme of the Holy Spirit being poured out. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Spirit in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 40, 3, 11, 11, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism with the Holy Ghost. Acts 11:16 recalls Jesus'' promise of this baptism, which is directly referenced in Matthew 3:11 as part of John''s proclamation about Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 42, 3, 16, 16, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism with the Holy Ghost. Acts 11:16 recalls Jesus'' promise of this baptism, while Luke 3:16 presents John the Baptist''s declaration of it, linking the two teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 43, 14, 26, 26, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Holy Spirit Teachings', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Ghost in teaching and remembrance. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Holy Spirit in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 26, 36, 25, 25, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Cleansing and Baptism Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of cleansing through water and the Holy Spirit. Both passages emphasize a transformative process, where water symbolizes purification and the Holy Spirit signifies a deeper spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 44, 10, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Baptism and Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the Holy Spirit. Acts 11:17 refers to the gift given by God, while Acts 10:47 discusses baptism for those who received the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 45, 9, 20, 26, 'who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Divine Authority and Inclusion', 'Both passages emphasize God''s sovereignty in choosing whom to bless and include in His people. Acts 11:17 reflects on God''s gift to Gentiles, while Romans 9:20-26 discusses God''s authority over creation and His purpose in calling both Jews and Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 18, 33, 13, 13, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Authority and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of human submission to God''s will. Both passages emphasize the idea that resisting God is futile, as He does not provide explanations for His actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 27, 4, 35, 35, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Sovereignty and Authority', 'This connection highlights God''s ultimate authority over human actions. Both passages emphasize that none can withstand God''s will or question His decisions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 44, 15, 8, 9, 'the like gift as he did unto us', 'Connection of God''s Gift', 'Both passages emphasize that God gave the Holy Spirit to both Jews and Gentiles, highlighting the equality of believers. This connection illustrates the theme of divine acceptance and purification through faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 45, 11, 34, 36, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Authority and Gifts', 'This connection highlights the sovereignty of God in bestowing gifts and the humility of humans in recognizing His authority. Both passages emphasize that all things are from God and that humans cannot withstand His will.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 18, 9, 12, 14, NULL, 'Divine Authority and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of human inability to resist God''s will. Both passages emphasize the futility of opposing God''s actions, as seen in Job''s acknowledgment of God''s sovereignty and Peter''s recognition of God''s gifts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 45, 10, 12, 13, 'God also to the Gentiles granted repentance', 'Salvation for All People', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s offer of salvation to both Jews and Gentiles. Both passages emphasize that repentance and calling upon the Lord lead to salvation for all, regardless of ethnicity.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 47, 7, 10, 10, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance leading to salvation. Both passages emphasize that repentance is a divine gift that results in life and salvation.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 26, 36, 26, 26, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Heart Transformation', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting repentance, while Ezekiel 36:26 promises a new heart, indicating a divine change in individuals.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 44, 20, 21, 21, 'repentance unto life', 'Connection of Repentance Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance as a pivotal element in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting ''repentance unto life'' to the Gentiles, while Acts 20:21 emphasizes ''repentance toward God'' for both Jews and Greeks.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 24, 31, 18, 20, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting ''repentance unto life,'' while Jeremiah 31:18-20 describes Ephraim''s process of turning and repenting, emphasizing God''s mercy towards him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 44, 5, 31, 31, 'repentance', 'Repentance and Forgiveness Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of repentance, with Acts 11:18 stating that God granted repentance to the Gentiles, while Acts 5:31 highlights that God gives repentance to Israel. This connection highlights the inclusive nature of God''s offer of repentance and forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 49, 3, 5, 8, 'Then hath God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life', 'Gentiles and God''s Promise', 'This connection highlights the inclusion of Gentiles in God''s plan for salvation. Both passages emphasize that Gentiles are granted repentance and are fellow heirs of the promise in Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 19, 44, 4, 36, 36, 'Cyprus', 'Connection through Cyprus and Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Cyprus as a significant location. In Acts 11:19, the scattered believers traveled to Cyprus while preaching, and in Acts 4:36, Barnabas is identified as being from Cyprus, linking him to the early ministry efforts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 19, 44, 15, 3, 3, 'Phenice', 'Spread of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the geographical continuity of the early church''s mission. Both passages mention Phenice, indicating a progression from preaching to Jews only to the inclusion of Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 19, 40, 10, 6, 6, 'preaching the word to none but unto the Jews only', 'Connection of Mission Focus', 'Both passages emphasize the focus on the Jews. Acts 11:19 mentions preaching to none but the Jews, aligning with Matthew 10:6''s directive to go to the lost sheep of Israel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 19, 43, 7, 35, 35, NULL, 'Connection of Dispersion and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of dispersion among the Jews and the teaching of the word. Acts 11:19 mentions those scattered due to persecution, while John 7:35 refers to the Jews questioning whether Jesus would go to the dispersed among the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 19, 48, 2, 11, 11, 'Antioch', 'Connection between Antioch and Peter', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Antioch in early Christian ministry. Acts 11:19 mentions the preaching in Antioch, while Galatians 2:11 highlights Peter''s actions there, indicating Antioch''s role as a pivotal location for early church dynamics.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 40, 27, 32, 32, 'men of Cyprus and Cyrene', 'Connection of Cyrene in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the presence of Cyrene in both passages. In Acts, men from Cyrene preach Jesus, while in Matthew, a man from Cyrene bears the cross of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 44, 13, 1, 1, 'Cyrene', 'Connection of Antioch''s Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of individuals from Cyrene in Antioch. The mention of Lucius of Cyrene in Acts 13:1 connects to the earlier reference of men from Cyrene preaching in Acts 11:20.', 'keyword', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 44, 2, 10, 10, 'Cyrene', 'Connection Between Antioch and Cyrene', 'This connection highlights the presence of men from Cyrene in both passages. Acts 11:20 mentions men from Cyrene preaching in Antioch, while Acts 2:10 lists Cyrene as part of the regions where Jews were present during Pentecost.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 46, 1, 23, 24, 'preaching the Lord Jesus', 'Preaching Christ to Greeks', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching Christ to the Greeks. Both passages emphasize the response to the message of Jesus, with Acts mentioning the preaching of the Lord Jesus and 1 Corinthians discussing the perception of Christ among Greeks.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 49, 3, 8, 8, 'preaching the Lord Jesus', 'Preaching to the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching to the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing the message of Jesus with non-Jewish audiences.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 43, 7, 35, 35, NULL, 'Connection of Gentile Outreach', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of preaching to the Gentiles. Acts 11:20 mentions preaching to the Grecians, while John 7:35 questions whether Jesus will go to the dispersed among the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 20, 46, 2, 2, 2, 'preaching the Lord Jesus', 'Preaching Jesus Christ Connection', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on preaching Jesus Christ in both passages. Acts 11:20 mentions preaching the Lord Jesus, while 1 Corinthians 2:2 focuses on knowing Jesus Christ and him crucified.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 42, 1, 66, 66, 'the hand of the Lord was with', 'Divine Presence and Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the active presence of the Lord in significant moments. In Acts, the hand of the Lord leads many to believe, while in Luke, it signifies the divine purpose surrounding the child.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 44, 2, 47, 47, 'the hand of the Lord', 'Growth of the Early Church', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Lord in adding believers to the church. Acts 11:21 mentions ''the hand of the Lord'' being with them, while Acts 2:47 states ''the Lord added to the church daily.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 44, 5, 14, 14, 'believed, and turned unto the Lord', 'Growth of Believers in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the increase of believers turning to the Lord. Acts 11:21 mentions a ''great number believed,'' while Acts 5:14 states that ''believers were the more added to the Lord.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 23, 59, 1, 1, 'the hand of the Lord', 'Divine Hand and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s active involvement in salvation. Both passages emphasize the power of the Lord''s hand in bringing belief and deliverance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 46, 3, 6, 7, 'the hand of the Lord was with them', 'Divine Influence on Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God in bringing about belief and growth. Acts highlights that ''the hand of the Lord was with them,'' while 1 Corinthians states ''God gave the increase,'' illustrating the divine influence in the process of faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 52, 1, 5, 5, 'the hand of the Lord was with them', 'Power of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the transformative power of the Lord''s presence in both passages. Acts 11:21 speaks of many turning to the Lord, while 1 Thessalonians 1:5 emphasizes the gospel''s power and assurance, suggesting a shared theme of divine influence leading to belief.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 21, 14, 30, 12, 12, 'the hand of the Lord', 'Divine Influence on Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the ''hand'' of God influencing people''s hearts and actions. In Acts, it leads to belief and turning to the Lord, while in 2 Chronicles, it unites Judah to follow God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 22, 44, 9, 27, 27, 'Barnabas', 'Barnabas'' Role in Early Church', 'This connection highlights Barnabas'' involvement in the early church. In Acts 11:22, he is sent to Antioch, while in Acts 9:27, he advocates for Saul, emphasizing his supportive role in the spread of the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 22, 44, 4, 36, 37, 'Barnabas', 'Connection Between Barnabas References', 'This connection highlights the role of Barnabas in the early church. In Acts 11:22, Barnabas is sent to Antioch, while Acts 4:36-37 introduces him as a key figure who supported the apostles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 22, 44, 8, 14, 14, 'sent forth Barnabas', 'Sending Leaders to New Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the church in Jerusalem to reports of new believers. In each case, the apostles or church leaders are sent to strengthen and support these communities.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 22, 44, 11, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Gentile Reception', 'Both passages emphasize the spread of the word of God to the Gentiles. The news of Gentiles receiving the word prompts the church in Jerusalem to send Barnabas to Antioch.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 22, 52, 3, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Good Tidings', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving good news. In Acts, Barnabas is sent to bring tidings to the church, while in 1 Thessalonians, Timothy brings good tidings of faith and charity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 46, 15, 58, 58, 'cleave unto the Lord', 'Steadfastness in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being steadfast in faith and commitment to the Lord. Acts 11:23 encourages believers to ''cleave unto the Lord,'' while 1 Corinthians 15:58 calls for being ''stedfast, unmoveable'' in their work for Him.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 44, 14, 22, 22, 'exhorted them all', 'Exhortation to Faithfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of exhortation to remain steadfast in faith. Acts 11:23 encourages believers to ''cleave unto the Lord,'' while Acts 14:22 urges them to ''continue in the faith.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 44, 13, 43, 43, 'grace of God', 'Connection of Grace and Exhortation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of continuing in the grace of God. In Acts 11:23, believers are encouraged to cleave unto the Lord, while in Acts 13:43, they are persuaded to continue in the grace of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 55, 3, 10, 10, 'purpose of heart', 'Purpose and Commitment to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of purpose in both passages. In Acts, believers are encouraged to ''cleave unto the Lord,'' while in 2 Timothy, the emphasis is on the ''purpose'' of the speaker''s life and doctrine.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 5, 10, 20, 20, 'cleave unto the Lord', 'Cleave to the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of cleaving to the Lord. Acts 11:23 encourages believers to cleave unto the Lord, while Deuteronomy 10:20 instructs to cleave to God as part of serving Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 5, 30, 20, 20, 'cleave unto the Lord', 'Cleave Unto the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of cleaving unto the Lord. Acts 11:23 reflects the encouragement to remain steadfast in faith, paralleling Deuteronomy 30:20''s call to love and obey God by cleaving to Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 23, 6, 23, 8, 8, 'cleave unto the Lord', 'Cleave unto the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of cleaving unto the Lord. Acts 11:23 encourages believers to purposefully cling to God, while Joshua 23:8 directly instructs the people to cleave to Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 44, 5, 14, 14, 'added unto the Lord', 'Growth of Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of believers being added to the Lord. Acts 11:24 highlights the role of a good man in this process, while Acts 5:14 notes the addition of multitudes of both men and women.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 44, 11, 21, 21, 'much people was added unto the Lord', 'Connection of Belief and Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of believers as a result of divine influence. Acts 11:21 notes that ''the hand of the Lord was with them,'' leading to many believing, while Acts 11:24 highlights the role of a good man, full of the Holy Ghost and faith, in adding to the number of believers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 19, 112, 5, 5, 'good man', 'Connection of Goodness and Discretion', 'Both passages emphasize the qualities of a ''good man.'' Acts highlights his goodness leading to faith and growth, while Psalms describes a good man showing favor and guiding affairs with discretion. This connection highlights the moral character and positive influence of a good man.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 10, 18, 27, 27, 'a good man', 'Good Men and Good Tidings', 'This connection highlights the characterization of individuals as ''good men'' in both passages. In Acts, the emphasis is on being filled with the Holy Spirit and faith, while in 2 Samuel, the focus is on bringing good news.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 45, 15, 15, 15, 'full of the Holy Ghost and of faith', 'Connection of Grace and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace and faith in the growth of the church. Acts highlights the faith of a good man, while Romans reflects on the grace given to Paul, suggesting a link between faith and divine grace in community building.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 19, 37, 23, 23, 'good man', 'Connection of Goodness and Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize the quality of being a ''good man'' and suggest that such individuals are favored by God. Acts 11:24 highlights the impact of a good man on others, while Psalms 37:23 assures that the Lord guides the steps of good men.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 24, 20, 12, 2, 2, 'good man', 'Connection of Goodness and Favor', 'Both passages emphasize the quality of being a ''good man'' and its connection to divine favor. Acts 11:24 describes a good man filled with faith, while Proverbs 12:2 states that a good man obtains favor from the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 25, 44, 9, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Saul''s Location', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s identity as being from Tarsus. Acts 11:25 mentions Barnabas seeking Saul, while Acts 9:11 identifies Saul as ''of Tarsus.'' This connection highlights the significance of Saul''s origin in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 25, 44, 9, 27, 27, 'to seek Saul', 'Barnabas and Saul''s Relationship', 'This connection highlights Barnabas''s role in seeking Saul, who had previously preached boldly at Damascus. Both passages emphasize Barnabas''s supportive actions towards Saul''s ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 25, 44, 9, 30, 30, 'to Tarsus', 'Barnabas and Saul''s Journey', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s connection to Tarsus. Acts 11:25 shows Barnabas seeking Saul, while Acts 9:30 mentions Saul being sent to Tarsus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 25, 44, 21, 39, 39, 'Tarsus', 'Connection of Tarsus and Paul', 'This connection highlights the significance of Tarsus as the origin of Saul, who later becomes Paul. Both passages emphasize his identity as a man from Tarsus, linking his early life to his later ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 26, 60, 4, 16, 16, 'called Christians first in Antioch', 'Connection of Christian Identity', 'This connection highlights the identity of believers as ''Christians'' in both passages. Acts 11:26 introduces the term, while 1 Peter 4:16 addresses the experience of suffering as a Christian.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 26, 44, 26, 28, 28, 'called Christians first in Antioch', 'Connection of Christian Identity', 'This connection highlights the emergence of the term ''Christian'' as a significant identity marker for believers. Both passages emphasize the use of ''Christian'' in different contexts, illustrating its importance in the early church.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 26, 40, 28, 19, 19, 'taught much people', 'Discipleship and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of teaching and making disciples. Both passages emphasize the importance of teaching people about faith, with Acts noting the disciples'' efforts in Antioch and Matthew commanding to teach all nations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
